***telegram Installation on kali****
 sudo apt-get install telegram-desktop
 ##you are done withit
 
 ***Burpsuite Istallation process******
1. Unzip the file 
2. Make A Folder On Desktop (I called my "burp")
3. Open Terminal And Install OpenJDK On v14:
sudo apt install openjdk-14* 

With the "*".

4. Start Burpsuite Accept License And Wait For Activation Window
java -javaagent:BurpSuiteLoader_v2020.11.2.jar -noverify -jar burpsuite_pro_v2020.11.2.jar

5. Load The Loader 
java -jar burploader-old.jar

6. Copy The Key From Loader & Paste It On Burp Window

7. Click "Manual Activation" And Get The Request Data And Paste It On Loader "Activation Request".

8. Copy Activation Response And Paste On Professional Version BOOM Activated 

9.alias burp='cd ~/Downloads/burp/burp && java -javaagent:BurpSuiteLoader_v2020.11.jar -noverify -jar burpsuite_pro_v2020.11.jar'

